HEADWORD: Scissure
<hw>Scis"sure</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scissura</ets>, from <ets>scindere</ets>, <ets>scissum</ets>, to
cut, split.]</ety> <def>A longitudinal opening in a body, made by
cutting; a cleft; a fissure.</def> <rj><au>Hammond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scitamineous</ent>⟦br⟧
